description: {"blocks":[{"key":"grfc","text":"This protocol describes the sample preparation to perform SMLM on midbrain dopaminergic neurons using phalloidin and a DNA aptamer in a combination of STORM and DNA-PAINT. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"3upem","text":"It also describes the experimental set up on the microscopy with the image acquisition details.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"6d9mn","text":"For single molecule localisation microscopy (SMLM), neurons were grown on glass coated ibidi chambers.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"53lja","text":"Once neurons reached the desired age, they were washed once in PBS","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"2n03i","text":"They are then fixed for    in 4% paraformaldehyde + 0.1% glutaraldehyde (both from Electron Microscopy Services) in PBS at room temperature.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":24,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"4b1vb","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"duration","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"duration":900,"guid":"10E5C6E039A311EDBE164D9C65AAE289","id":0,"label":"","pause":null,"preset":[],"start":null}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"p7mo","text":"The neurons were then reduced in 0.1% sodium borohydride (Sigma) in PBS for   at room temperature.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":76,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"f0jo9","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"duration","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"duration":420,"guid":"2D26E69039A311EDBE164D9C65AAE289","id":0,"label":"","pause":null,"preset":[],"start":null}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"3i9ta","text":"To label cells with the DNA-aptamer and phalloidin, after fixation and PBS washes, cells were permeabilised with 0.25% triton X-100 in PBS for    at room temperature","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":143,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"4cm9a","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"duration","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"duration":600,"guid":"7B6FF26039A311EDBE164D9C65AAE289","id":0,"label":"","pause":null,"preset":[],"start":null}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"f3sch","text":"The cells were then blocked in blocking solution (0.1% triton X-100, 10% normal goat serum (Abcam), 10% salmon sperm DNA (Thermo Fisher Scientific)) in PBS for    at room temperature","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":160,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"ehv8t","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"duration","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"duration":7200,"guid":"9802666039A311EDBE164D9C65AAE289","id":0,"label":"","pause":null,"preset":[],"start":null}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"eo5u1","text":"The samples were then incubated with 100 nM of the DNA-aptamer made up in the blocking solution at   overnight. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":99,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"a5qs5","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":1,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"40lk","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"8sat1","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"temperature","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"error_temperature":false,"guid":"C322BE8039A311EDBE164D9C65AAE289","id":0,"label":"","scientificNotation":false,"temperature":"4","unit":10}},"1":{"type":"notes","mutability":"IMMUTABLE","data":{"blocks":[{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"257ib","text":"Aptamer binds to beta-sheet rich structures including protein aggregates. The sequence of the aptamer is: GCCTGTGGTGTTGGGGCGGGTGCGTTATACATCTA (ATD Bio).","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}}}}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"f6p2a","text":"After incubation, cells were washed 1x in PBS","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"dqglc","text":"They are then incubated with phalloidin-647 (1:400) (Thermo Fisher Scientific) made up in the blocking solution for   at room temperature.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":116,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"38mmc","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"duration","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"duration":3600,"guid":"1BFDEFC039A411EDBE164D9C65AAE289","id":0,"label":"","pause":null,"preset":[],"start":null}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"d60cj","text":"Cells were then washed 1x in PBS and either imaged, or incubated with DAPI (1:10000) in PBS for    at room temperature followed by 2x PBS washes before imaging.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":96,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"1a55t","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"duration","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"duration":600,"guid":"3947A5D039A411EDBE164D9C65AAE289","id":0,"label":"","pause":null,"preset":[],"start":null}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"uais","text":"Cells were lysed mechanically in PBS before being centrifuged at   .","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":65,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"7ru49","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"centrifuge","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"centrifuge":"3600","duration":300,"error_centrifuge":false,"error_temperature":false,"guid":"669C913039A411EDBE164D9C65AAE289","id":0,"label":"","pause":null,"preset":[],"scientificNotation":{"centrifuge":false,"temperature":false},"start":null,"temperature":"4","temperatureUnit":10,"unit":34}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"af65h","text":"The supernatant was collected and the protein concentration was quantified using the BCA Protein Assay Kit (Thermo Fisher Scientific).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"cdd5v","text":"22 x 40 mm, 1 mm thick glass slides, were cleaned with an argon plasma for    before 22x22 gaskets (Bio-Rad) were affixed to the surface to create a well.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":75,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"dq3pi","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"duration","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"duration":3600,"guid":"913B5D4039A411EDBE164D9C65AAE289","id":0,"label":"","pause":null,"preset":[],"start":null}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"aae2f","text":"Cell lysate was diluted 1 in 10 with filtered PBS (0.02 μm) and added to the glass slides","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"elaip","text":"100 nM DNA-aptamer was added to the glass slide and incubated with lysate for   .","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":78,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"e1krt","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"7hmh3","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":1,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"8ajh2","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"duration","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"duration":600,"guid":"D21D51B039A411EDBE164D9C65AAE289","id":0,"label":"","pause":null,"preset":[],"start":null}},"1":{"type":"notes","mutability":"IMMUTABLE","data":{"blocks":[{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"far9i","text":"Aptamer sequence: GCCTGTGGTGTTGGGGCGGGTGCGTTACCACCACCACCACCACCA (ATD Bio)","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"2jptk","text":"Sample was then washed off with filtered PBS three times before imaging","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"b30lb","text":"SMLM was performed on a Nanoimager super-resolution microscope (Oxford Nanoimaging Ltd) equipped with an Olympus 1.4 NA 100x oil immersion super apochromatic objective. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"82n8m","text":"To ensure efficient stochastic blinking for STORM (AF647-tagged phalloidin), the samples were incubated with a blinking induction buffer (B cubed, ONI).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"8ij9f","text":"Separately to this, AD-PAINT was also employed which relies on the addition of an imaging oligonucleotide strand","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"991e","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"c3t4m","text":" to the buffer. 1 nM of the imaging strand was added to the B cubed buffer before imaging. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"61jm6","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"avm8u","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"fuo55","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"notes","mutability":"IMMUTABLE","data":{"blocks":[{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"65mgo","text":"sequence: CCAGATGTAT-CY3B","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"fo4dh","text":"The laser illumination angle was set to 51o for all imaging leading to total internal reflection fluorescence (TIRF).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"sup","offset":42,"length":1}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"f35kh","text":"AF647-tagged phalloidin was first imaged for 4000-8000 frames using the 640 nm laser (80% power). After this, 4000-5000 frames at 30% power for the 561 nm laser was used to image and super-resolve the aptamer. Both were recorded at a frame-rate of 50 ms. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"52tp0","text":"For imaging aggregates in neuronal lysate using AD-PAINT, 2 nM of the imaging strand was added. Images were acquired on Oxford Nanoimager at 20 frames s-1, for 8000 frames (20% 635 nm laser power, TIRF).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"sup","offset":152,"length":4}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"29q5l","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"368ob","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"dtemu","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"notes","mutability":"IMMUTABLE","data":{"blocks":[{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"8gvgc","text":"sequence: GGTGGT-ATTO 655","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}}}}}
